{{Quote|Have you ever heard of the Sennex? They're a bad lot, worse than the Hutts, and I say that with all due respect. They're slave traders.|[[Ephant Mon/Legends|Ephant Mon]], to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:JPEM" />}}
The '''Sennex''' or '''Sennex Pirates''' were [[Slavery/Legends|slave traders]]<ref name="SWG:JPEM" /> from the [[Sennex system/Legends|Sennex system]].<ref name="Planetnamia" /> They were considered among the most despicable [[Pirate/Legends|pirates]] in [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]] during the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="SWG:JPEM" />

==History==
{{Quote|Sennex are causing trouble, bringing heat to the planet, and Jabba doesn't like it. Start thinning the Sennex herd, will you?|Ephant Mon, to a spacer|<ref name="SWG:JPEM" />}}
[[File:SennexLookout.jpg|thumb|right|150px|A Sennex lookout.]]
By the time of the fall of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]], [[Aurra Sing/Legends|Aurra Sing]] was once in their possession before she took up the [[Bounty hunter/Legends|bounty hunting]] business. The pirates told her the [[The Dark Woman|Dark Woman]] had purposely abandoned her before they sold her to [[Wallanooga]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]].<ref name="Card">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=swtcg/article/charactersaurrasing|text=Behind the Cards: Aurra Sing}}</ref>

In [[1 ABY/Legends|1 ABY]],<ref name="SWG_timeline">{{SWG_timeline}}</ref> [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] the Hutt was bothered by their presence on [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] and sent some of his henchmen to harass the Sennex and remind them who was the true ruler of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]. [[Ephant Mon/Legends|Ephant Mon]] thus hired some spacers to eliminate five Sennex slavemasters and nine Sennex guards in the [[Sennex Compound|their compound]] and wipe all their databanks.<ref name="SWG:JPEM" /> Nevertheless, a Sennex [[Spy/Legends|spy]] known as [[Romo Vax]] managed to infiltrate [[Jabba's criminal empire/Legends|Jabba Desilijic Tiure's criminal empire]]. He was eventually killed in his [[Romo Vax's Hideout|hideout]] by one of [[Bib Fortuna/Legends|Bib Fortuna's]] henchmen.<ref name="SWG:JPBF">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Jabba's Palace : Bib Fortuna|Tatooine}}</ref>

In the meantime, Sennex pirates kidnapped the wife and daughter of a Tatooine [[Moisture farmer/Legends|moisture farmer]] and held them captive inside a [[Beetle Cave|cave]] for ransom. They were eventually [[Quest of the Hero of Tatooine|freed]] by an individual known as the [[Hero of Tatooine]].<ref name="SWG:TMotH" />

The Sennex also had a [[Sennex Slave Bunker|slave bunker]] near [[Anchorhead/Legends|Anchorhead]], posing as a research facility. [[Huff Darklighter]] who was fully aware of the illicit activities, tasked a spacer with disrupting their operations.<ref name="SWG:DE">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Darklighter Estate|Tatooine}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The Sennex appeared in the [[2003]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars Galaxies]]'', a [[Wikipedia:Massively multiplayer online role-playing game|massively multiplayer online roleplaying game]] developed by [[Sony]] Online Entertainment and published by [[LucasArts]],<ref name="SWG:TMotH" /> prior to its closure on [[December 15]], [[2011]].<ref name="Shutdown">{{SonyCite|url=playerinfo|text=IMPORTANT INFORMATION ABOUT ''STAR WARS'' GALAXIES™}}</ref>

